The paper deals with communication complexity, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and falls under the category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also involves probability and information theory, which are subfields of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of exponential decay in the success probability suggests a connection to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and the characterization of communication complexity may also be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
